{
  "name": "spinphony",
  "description": "Spinphony is an ECE 3140 final project that turns computer audio into live motor music: a Python host pipeline captures system audio, detects notes with an STFT, and streams motor frequency frames over USB-UART to an FRDM-KL46Z microcontroller, which drives four NEMA17 stepper motors through DRV8825 drivers to act as a rough electromechanical speaker.",
